---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import CaseHeader from '../../components/CaseHeader.astro';
import CaseSection from '../../components/CaseSection.astro';
import Gallery from '../../components/Gallery.astro';
import RelatedWriting from '../../components/RelatedWriting.astro';
import { getProject } from '../../data/projects';
import { treaxeShots } from '../../data/treaxeShots';
import { site } from '../../data/site';
import { asset } from '../../lib/url';

const project = getProject('treaxe')!;

// The full lifecycle the product follows — straight from the case study.
const flow = [
  'Lead', 'Estimate / Bid', 'Signed Proposal', 'Project Setup', 'Schedule & Tasks',
  'Materials & POs', 'Equipment', 'Daily Logs & Photos', 'Change Orders',
  'Invoice', 'Payment', 'Client Portal',
];
---
<Base
  title={`TreAxe — Construction Operations SaaS · ${site.name}`}
  description="A production construction-operations platform connecting the whole job lifecycle from first lead to final payment. Co-built and co-owned with a collaborator."
>
  <CaseHeader project={project} />

  <div class="shell case-wrap">
    <!-- Lifecycle strip: the connective-tissue thesis, visualized -->
    <section class="flow reveal" aria-label="Job lifecycle">
      <p class="kicker flow-kicker">/ One connected workflow</p>
      <div class="flow-track">
        {flow.map((step, i) => (
          <>
            <span class="flow-step font-mono">{step}</span>
            {i < flow.length - 1 && <span class="flow-arrow" aria-hidden="true">→</span>}
          </>
        ))}
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Walkthrough video: a quick animated tour of the real product screens.
         Offline-rendered MP4 (Hyperframes), committed as a static asset — base-aware via asset(). -->
    <section id="walkthrough" class="demo-video reveal" aria-label="Product walkthrough">
      <p class="kicker wt-kicker">/ Walkthrough</p>
      <div class="dv-frame">
        <video
          controls
          muted
          playsinline
          preload="none"
          poster={asset('treaxe/walkthrough.poster.jpg')}
          class="dv-el"
        >
          <source src={asset('treaxe/walkthrough.mp4')} type="video/mp4" />
          Your browser does not support the video tag.
          <a href={asset('treaxe/walkthrough.mp4')}>Download the walkthrough (MP4)</a>.
        </video>
      </div>
      <p class="dv-cap font-mono">▶ A 26-second tour — dashboard, CRM pipeline, estimates, invoices, projects, and an auto-built proposal.</p>
    </section>

    <CaseSection num="01" title="The problem">
      <p>
        Construction back-offices leak money in the gaps <em>between</em> tools: a bid wins
        but the project never gets set up cleanly, materials get ordered against the wrong
        budget, change orders go un-billed, invoices slip.
      </p>
      <p>
        The value isn't any single feature — it's that the <strong>whole workflow is
        connected</strong>, so a signed estimate becomes a project becomes an invoice
        without anyone re-keying data or dropping a step.
      </p>
    </CaseSection>

    <CaseSection num="02" title="What it is">
      <p>
        TreAxe is a production construction-operations platform for small-to-mid contractors —
        the kind of crews who run the whole business out of a truck, a phone, and a pile of
        spreadsheets. It replaces that sprawl with one role-aware app that follows a job across
        its entire life.
      </p>
      <p>
        That's roughly <strong>42 screens</strong> covering CRM, estimating with line items
        and e-signatures, scheduling and time tracking, procurement, field documentation,
        invoicing, and a client-facing portal — all multi-tenant, all under row-level security.
      </p>
    </CaseSection>

    <CaseSection num="03" title="How it works">
      <p>
        The frontend is React + Vite + TypeScript with a layered architecture —
        <strong>pages → context → services → Supabase</strong> — so business logic stays out
        of components. Global state lives in typed context providers (auth/roles, all business
        entities, and English/Spanish i18n for bilingual crews). Every entity has its own CRUD
        service over the Supabase client.
      </p>
      <p>
        The backend is <strong>Supabase Postgres</strong> with <strong>row-level security on
        every table</strong>, multi-tenant by <code>org_id</code> — a contractor only ever sees
        their own data, enforced at the database, not the UI. All external side-effects are
        isolated behind <strong>Supabase Edge Functions</strong> (Deno):
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Payments</strong> — Stripe Checkout for one-time invoice payments (card / ACH) and org subscriptions, with a server-side invoice status state machine so a payment can't leave an invoice inconsistent.</li>
        <li><strong>Email</strong> — Gmail send via the user's stored OAuth token (auto-refreshing), used for estimates, change orders, and invoices, every send logged to an activity trail.</li>
        <li><strong>Material pricing</strong> — live producer-price-index lookups (24h cached) so estimates use real market rates.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        It ships continuously: pushing to <code>main</code> auto-deploys to production
        (<a href="https://www.treaxe.io" target="_blank" rel="noopener">www.treaxe.io</a>) via
        Vercel, gated by a Playwright suite — unit tests, end-to-end journeys against a live
        environment, and a post-deploy smoke check on the critical path.
      </p>
    </CaseSection>

    <CaseSection num="04" title="Engineering depth">
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Security at the data layer</strong> — RLS policies, not just app-level checks; the multi-tenant boundary holds even if the UI is bypassed.</li>
        <li><strong>Hardened auth</strong> — the Supabase client uses an in-process lock instead of the browser Web Locks API, fixing a class of sign-in deadlocks that only appear on real (non-incognito) browsers — the kind of bug that passes every clean-profile test and still breaks production.</li>
        <li><strong>Honest tests</strong> — journey tests assert the <em>real</em> outcome (the row persisted, the email actually sent) rather than a green status pill, with no silent skips.</li>
      </ul>
    </CaseSection>

    <CaseSection num="05" title="Role & context">
      <!-- TODO: confirm exact role split with the collaborator (e.g. estimating, payments,
           client portal, infra) so this reads precisely. Co-ownership stated honestly. -->
      <p>
        Co-built with a collaborator — we own the codebase
        together. This is a collaboration, not a solo project.
      </p>
    </CaseSection>

    <!-- Demo access callout. NOTE: the hands-on demo is gated on request rather than
         publishing static credentials — a previously-published staging login stopped
         authenticating ("Invalid email or password"), and minting/confirming a working
         demo login lives on the (co-owned) TreAxe side, not in this repo. The walkthrough
         video above is the always-working way to see the product. -->
    <section class="demo-box reveal" aria-label="Demo access">
      <div class="demo-head">
        <p class="kicker">/ See it live</p>
        <h2 class="display demo-h">A fully-seeded demo on synthetic data.</h2>
        <p class="demo-sub">
          The 26-second walkthrough above tours the real product end to end. Want to click
          through it yourself? Hands-on access to an isolated demo instance — synthetic data,
          no real customer records — is available on request.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="demo-cred">
        <a href={`mailto:${site.email}?subject=TreAxe%20demo%20access`} class="btn btn-primary demo-cta">
          Request demo access <span aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
        </a>
        <a href="#walkthrough" class="demo-secondary link-spark font-mono">Or rewatch the walkthrough ↑</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Screenshot gallery — empty until the orchestrator fills treaxeShots.ts.
         Renders nothing while the array is empty (see Gallery component). -->
    <Gallery shots={treaxeShots} label="Product screens" />

    <!-- Related writing: articles tagged `treaxe`. The article lives in /writing;
         it only surfaces here. Renders nothing if there are no matches. -->
    <RelatedWriting slug="treaxe" />

    <nav class="case-next reveal" aria-label="Next project">
      <a href={import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '') + '/work/nucleus'} class="next-link">
        <span class="next-k font-mono">Next →</span>
        <span class="next-title display">Nucleus</span>
      </a>
    </nav>
  </div>
</Base>

<style>
  .case-wrap { position: relative; z-index: 2; padding-top: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3.5rem); }

  .flow { padding-bottom: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-line); margin-bottom: clamp(1rem, 3vw, 2rem); }
  .flow-kicker { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
  .flow-track { display: flex; flex-wrap: wrap; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem 0.7rem; }
  .flow-step {
    font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--color-paper-dim);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-line-2); border-radius: 2px;
    padding: 0.4rem 0.7rem; background: var(--color-ink-2);
    transition: border-color 0.2s ease, color 0.2s ease;
  }
  .flow-step:hover { border-color: var(--color-amber); color: var(--color-paper); }
  .flow-arrow { color: var(--color-amber); opacity: 0.6; font-size: 0.85rem; }

  /* Walkthrough video — amber-toned to match TreAxe (cf. FredGPT's teal demo frame) */
  .demo-video { margin: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem) 0 clamp(1rem, 3vw, 2rem); }
  .wt-kicker { margin-bottom: 1.2rem; }
  .dv-frame {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-line-2); border-radius: 3px; overflow: hidden;
    background: #000; position: relative;
    box-shadow: 0 30px 80px -40px rgba(0,0,0,0.9), 0 0 0 1px rgba(232,161,60,0.06);
  }
  .dv-frame::before {
    content: ""; position: absolute; inset: 0; pointer-events: none; z-index: 1;
    box-shadow: inset 0 0 120px -40px rgba(232,161,60,0.16);
  }
  .dv-el { display: block; width: 100%; height: auto; aspect-ratio: 16 / 9; background: #000; }
  .dv-cap { margin-top: 0.9rem; font-size: 0.76rem; color: var(--color-paper-mute); letter-spacing: 0.04em; }

  .demo-box {
    margin-top: clamp(3rem, 7vw, 5rem);
    border: 1px solid var(--color-line-2); border-radius: 3px;
    background:
      linear-gradient(180deg, rgba(232,161,60,0.05), transparent 60%),
      var(--color-ink-2);
    padding: clamp(1.6rem, 4vw, 2.8rem);
    display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1.1fr 0.9fr; gap: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem); align-items: center;
  }
  @media (max-width: 760px) { .demo-box { grid-template-columns: 1fr; } }
  .demo-h { font-size: clamp(1.5rem, 3.5vw, 2.3rem); color: var(--color-paper); margin: 0.8rem 0 0; line-height: 1.05; }
  .demo-sub { color: var(--color-paper-dim); margin: 1rem 0 0; font-size: 1rem; max-width: 44ch; }
  .demo-cta { margin-bottom: 1rem; }
  .demo-secondary { display: inline-block; font-size: 0.78rem; letter-spacing: 0.02em; color: var(--color-paper-mute); }
  .cred-list { margin: 0; }
  .cred-row { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 90px 1fr; gap: 0.8rem; padding: 0.7rem 0; border-top: 1px solid var(--color-line); align-items: baseline; }
  .cred-row dt { font-size: 0.66rem; letter-spacing: 0.16em; color: var(--color-paper-mute); margin: 0; }
  .cred-row dd { margin: 0; font-size: 0.92rem; color: var(--color-amber); word-break: break-all; }

  .case-next { margin-top: clamp(4rem, 9vw, 7rem); border-top: 1px solid var(--color-line); padding-top: 2.5rem; }
  .next-link { display: inline-flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; transition: transform 0.3s ease; }
  .next-link:hover { transform: translateX(8px); }
  .next-k { font-size: 0.78rem; color: var(--color-paper-mute); letter-spacing: 0.1em; }
  .next-title { font-size: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 3rem); color: var(--color-paper); }
  .next-link:hover .next-title { color: var(--color-amber); }

  /* inline code */
  .cs-body :global(code), code {
    font-family: var(--font-mono); font-size: 0.85em;
    background: var(--color-ink-3); border: 1px solid var(--color-line);
    padding: 0.08em 0.38em; border-radius: 2px; color: var(--color-paper);
  }
</style>
